    },
    {
      "id": "QGvChBoo6U8r-pJtvue5Y",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1823.3624628041619,
      "y": 60.228980195720396,
      "width": 1111,
      "height": 950,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b53",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1507199503,
      "version": 1870,
      "versionNonce": 1140226380,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770901007529,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "ChatGPT -> A LLM model, which will take a prompt and give result in real time. how it do this, due to\nChatGPT is trained on very large data\n\n\nNormal Model -> Speech recognition model -> we will train this model after training it give response\nin real time.\n\n\nLLM models are trained on very large data, thats why they know about everything\n\nlike ChatGPT knows about everything due to this LLM model is trained on very large data on diff diff \ndomains.\n\n\ndiff diff LLM models have their api exposed for ChatGPT, Gemini(Gema model), using this we can built\nour own product.\n\n\nUseCase -> Lets say we are creating Ecommerce website and in that Ecommerce website we have lot of\ninvoices pdf for many years, and we have to find price for sale item in these invoices. Here we can \nuse LLM models\nwe can write scraper that will fetch text for us, or we will pass this to LLM and that will give\ncontent to us.\n\nLLM models are very big so we can't execute those in our local machine , to run this we can use\ngroq(cloud) to run or execute our LLM model , here we can set whihc LLM model we need to use ,\n\nwe can use model from Google -> gemma\nor from Groq -> Groq\nor from Meta -> llama -> trained on 65 billion parameters\nor from OpenAI -> Wisper-large-v3\n\nMeta models are very good due to meta data good is better that Chatgpt data.\n\nwe can select model in groq which we want to use for LLM and ask questions\n\n\nWe will create a project in that we will integrate this LLM model ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "ChatGPT -> A LLM model, which will take a prompt and give result in real time. how it do this, due to\nChatGPT is trained on very large data\n\n\nNormal Model -> Speech recognition model -> we will train this model after training it give response\nin real time.\n\n\nLLM models are trained on very large data, thats why they know about everything\n\nlike ChatGPT knows about everything due to this LLM model is trained on very large data on diff diff \ndomains.\n\n\ndiff diff LLM models have their api exposed for ChatGPT, Gemini(Gema model), using this we can built\nour own product.\n\n\nUseCase -> Lets say we are creating Ecommerce website and in that Ecommerce website we have lot of\ninvoices pdf for many years, and we have to find price for sale item in these invoices. Here we can \nuse LLM models\nwe can write scraper that will fetch text for us, or we will pass this to LLM and that will give\ncontent to us.\n\nLLM models are very big so we can't execute those in our local machine , to run this we can use\ngroq(cloud) to run or execute our LLM model , here we can set whihc LLM model we need to use ,\n\nwe can use model from Google -> gemma\nor from Groq -> Groq\nor from Meta -> llama -> trained on 65 billion parameters\nor from OpenAI -> Wisper-large-v3\n\nMeta models are very good due to meta data good is better that Chatgpt data.\n\nwe can select model in groq which we want to use for LLM and ask questions\n\n\nWe will create a project in that we will integrate this LLM model ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "nbNqJKS9VzeZBglu3J5Zp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1831.3234003041619,
